text.tspan: Do one thing and do it well.
Jim Waldo tried to warn us*
There is no such thing as an RPC.
The is no such thing as a procedure.
We can't make an arbitary API remote.
Monoliths can't be broken up that way.
* A Note on Distributed Computing, Jim Waldo, Geoff Wyant, Ann Wollrath, Sam Kendal. 1994.
Is Mr Fowler right about "monolith first"* ?
What is a monolith? Is it a "standalone" application or the 3-tier form?
Instead of monolith, why not initially target siloed services?
Can we have monolith ease of deployment with siloed services?
What about with the single layer stateless pattern?
You can rewrite it if it is crufty.
You can use a different language or a different technology stack.
Feature scaling - add a new service for a new feature.
It is impossible to maintain coherent state
across a network in the presence of failures.
